![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/d48b4301-fba2-424b-84f0-8229af895280/Dwayne-Johnson-x-Mark-Kerr-121423-split-d65d91357dc14340a9a020bd8f4e8a20.jpg?format=original)

According to reports from ESPN, The Rock is set to dive straight into filming his next movie role in "The Smashing Machine” after Wrestlemania.

The Smashing Machine is an upcoming biographical drama film on the MMA and UFC legend Mark Kerr. A24 is producing the film, which will serve as the debut solo feature for director Benny Safdie. Starring Dwayne “The Rock” Johnson and Emily Blunt.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/3e38362d-8b9d-4498-8537-02bfa55391d0/dwayne-johnson-mark-kerr-121323-d9d14b0e46f94b829a16e0b4684388d2.jpg?format=original)

For The Rock, juggling the demands of both wrestling and acting is nothing short of a balancing act. Yet, his dedication to his craft and tireless work ethic continue to propel him to new heights of success in both arenas. As he transitions from the adrenaline-fueled world of WrestleMania to the disciplined environment of a film set, The Rock's ability to seamlessly navigate between these two worlds is a testament to his versatility as a performer.

While fans eagerly await updates on "The Smashing Machine" and The Rock's involvement in the project, one thing is certain: whether he's delivering spine-tingling promos in the wrestling ring or captivating audiences on the big screen, The Rock's magnetic presence and undeniable talent will continue to leave a lasting impression on audiences worldwide.

In the meantime, as The Rock embarks on his next cinematic adventure, fans can look forward to the excitement of WrestleMania XL.